{"words":[{"word":"poets","count":3},{"word":"sentinel","count":2},{"word":"oh","count":1},{"word":"parallels","count":1},{"word":"striking","count":1},{"word":"day","count":1},{"word":"society","count":1},{"word":"boarded","count":1},{"word":"sail","count":1},{"word":"ciaccona","count":1},{"word":"toccata","count":1},{"word":"blaspheming","count":1},{"word":"ha","count":1},{"word":"resonance","count":1},{"word":"babbled","count":1},{"word":"years","count":1},{"word":"another","count":1},{"word":"group","count":1},{"word":"fools","count":1},{"word":"ready","count":1},{"word":"march","count":1},{"word":"path","count":1},{"word":"always","count":1},{"word":"believe","count":1},{"word":"damn","count":1},{"word":"horse","count":1},{"word":"least","count":1},{"word":"clever","count":1},{"word":"enough","count":1},{"word":"hold","count":1},{"word":"tongues","count":1},{"word":"nerve","count":1},{"word":"parade","count":1},{"word":"blasphemy","count":1},{"word":"streets","count":1},{"word":"almost","count":1},{"word":"makes","count":1},{"word":"noble","count":1},{"word":"comparison","count":1},{"word":"spare","count":1},{"word":"sarcasm","count":1},{"word":"insolent","count":1},{"word":"bard","count":1},{"word":"nothing","count":1},{"word":"mouthy","count":1},{"word":"relic","count":1},{"word":"last","count":1},{"word":"remains","count":1},{"word":"wretched","count":1},{"word":"family","count":1},{"word":"repent","count":1},{"word":"crimes","count":1}],"lines":[{"text":"Oh, the parallels... so striking. Just like the day the Poets Society boarded their Sail. You, Ciaccona Toccata, blaspheming against the Sentinel.","quest_name":"Your Summer Will Never Wither","quest_id":165000003},{"text":"Ha! So this is the <i>resonance</i> they babbled on about? After all these years, another group of fools is ready to march down the same path.","quest_name":"Your Summer Will Never Wither","quest_id":165000003},{"text":"Why are there always those who believe the Sentinel is some damn horse?","quest_name":"Your Summer Will Never Wither","quest_id":165000003},{"text":"The poets were at least clever enough to hold their tongues. But you have the nerve to parade your blasphemy through the streets. It almost makes those poets look noble by comparison.","quest_name":"Your Summer Will Never Wither","quest_id":165000003},{"text":"Spare me your sarcasm, you insolent bard! You're nothing but a mouthy relic, the last of what remains of your wretched family! Do you not repent for your crimes?!","quest_name":"Your Summer Will Never Wither","quest_id":165000003}]}